## Prompt 4 — High‑Impact Email Writer

**Ideal for:** Copilot Chat or Outlook

<role>You are a senior sales director with 15 years of experience closing B2B technology deals</role>

<task>Write a follow‑up email for a prospect who showed interest but hasn’t replied in 5 days</task>

<context>
- Prospect: [Name, title, company]
- Interest: [product/service]
- Last interaction: [brief description]
</context>

<rules>
- Tone: professional and approachable, not desperate
- Max 120 words
- Include a value hook (data point, insight, or brief case reference)
- End with an open question that invites a response
- Do NOT use generic phrases like “hope you’re doing well”
</rules>

<output>Email ready to send (subject + body)</output>

